==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: r&#299;-fûr

===Etymology===
Middle English ''referren'', from Old French ''referer'', from Latin ''referre'' : ''re-'', ''re-'' + ''ferre'', to carry or, bear; see ''bher-'' in Indo-European Roots.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|refer|refers|referred|referring}}
#{{transitive}} To direct to a source for help or information.
#:''The shop assistant referred me to the help desk on ground floor.''
#To submit to an authority figure for consideration.
#To direct the attention of.

